description.narrative: (Lebanon): The Lebanon Industry Value Chain Development (LIVCD) develops functional value chains to increase incomes of the rural.populations, including micro, small, and medium enterprises, increases farmer.and other producer incomes, and enhances enterprises in rural areas, including.those affected by the Syrian crisis. FY 2017 funds will.also help tourism providers in rural areas to upgrade and improve their.services and expand their outreach. The.project is gearing its interventions towards encouraging the private.sector led activities to ensure sustainability. During the last 16 months of.the project, LIVCD will focus its efforts on its exit strategy for each value.chain, ensuring that the legacy of project interventions is embedded with.partner organizations and industry stakeholders across.Lebanon. The project will continue to actively facilitate its partners to.implement the innovative initiatives introduced during its previous five.years.
